OL,3,CTeenager campaigns for end to violence
OL,4,Cagainst women and girls
OL,6,FA teenager from Oxfordshire says more
OL,7,Fneeds to done to tackle violence and
OL,8,Fharassment against women and girls
OL,9,Fafter experiencing sexual assault.
OL,11,FNiamh Dernie, 17, has waived her right
OL,12,Fto anonymity and has been campaigning
OL,13,Ffor change for two years.
OL,15,FShe said: "My friends are cat-called
OL,16,Fdaily, I'm cat-called daily. It's
OL,17,Fsomething that I see weekly. I see it
OL,18,Fall the time. Some of my friends have
OL,19,Fbeen stalked. This sort of behaviour
OL,20,Fcan happen anywhere."
